Mr Nkabinde sadly lost his life on Monday evening after being hit by a truck whilst on duty. Mr Nkabinde joined the Mpumalanga Traffic Department in 1988, shortly after that, he was stationed in Delmas and worked for the overload control unit. In February 2000, he relocated to Middelburg and worked mainly at the weighbridge, sometimes attending to accident scenes and other traffic duties. His colleagues described him as a calm, peaceful and bubbly person who was hardworking and dedicated to his job. Mr Nkabinde is survived by his mother, wife, and two children. 